main event: Several unidentified aerial objects were sighted in the San Diego, California area during March 1952.
interesting points: The objects were described as flying at extremely high speeds and altitudes,The objects had a metallic appearance and varied in size from approximately 30 to 50 feet in length,There was no discernible method of propulsion visible on the objects,The objects were reported to leave no vapor trail,Several reliable observers from a private aircraft owners' club corroborated the sightings.
witness description: members of a private aircraft owners' club in San Diego, California
